The paper discusses load balancing in parallel applications, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of mathematical models to formalize the new approach suggests that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) or mathematical software (cs.MS) sub-categories. The application of the new approach to a fluid model with erosion suggests that the paper may also belong to the physics (cs.PF) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of the new approach compared to the standard load balancing method, which suggests that it may also belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
